----- stdout -----
BorrowChecker command-line interface

Usage: borrow-checker [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  account      Manage accounts (list, create, archive)
  transaction  Manage transactions (list, add, amend, void)
  import       Import transactions from a file using a named import profile
  export       Export all accounts and transactions to a file or stdout
  report       Generate financial reports
  budget       Manage budget envelopes (requires Milestone 5)
  plugin       Manage plugins (requires Milestone 6)
  completions  Generate shell completion scripts
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --json               Emit machine-readable JSON instead of human-readable output [env: BC_JSON=]
      --db-path <DB_PATH>  Path to the SQLite database file
  -v, --verbose...         Increase log verbosity
  -q, --quiet...           Decrease log verbosity
  -h, --help               Print help (see more with '--help')
  -V, --version            Print version
----- stderr -----
